posts.name: Blaine Pack
posts.cooked:
Code ran fine for 2021.   Updated PC to 2022 LabView.  Updated roboRio to 2022 Now any code won’t download to roboRio.  It gets so far and then says it can’t connect to target. This happens 19 times out of 20. Wireless off Tried 3 USB cables. Updated roboRio firmware from version 6 to 8 Tried a second roboRio. Made sure all anti-malware was turned off on the PC.

Before 2022 the same PC with the same roboRio loaded just fine…

I am out of suggestions.  Any help appreciated

posts.name: JeffB
posts.cooked: When did you update the firmware, before or after you were seeing issues?

posts.name: Tom Line
posts.cooked: We also encountered this issue.  We reformatted the Rio and reinstalled the third party libraries and that fixed it.

posts.name: Aidan Mundy
posts.cooked: We also had this issue, and resolved it in the same manner.

posts.name: Blaine Pack
posts.cooked:
Thanks for your reply.  We did the firmware first.    Then the 2022 stuff.  That is when the problems started.  Then we fell back to the previous firmware then loaded the 2022 stuff.

All was well before the upgrades.  Not sure how to procede

Same thing keeps happening to us even after updating firmware, reinstalling libraries, and restarting.

Does anyone know the root cause of this issue?

posts.name: Asher Olgeirson
posts.cooked: I might be giving you a bit of a red herring but have you tried using SSH to access the RoboRio to find the problem. I have ran into a few errors where it decided to change its IP address to something random. I know my suggestion only helps for wireless issues but if you are totally lost I guess it’s worth a shot.

posts.name: Blaine Pack
posts.cooked:
Thanks to all who replied.  I changed the target address from the DNS name to 172.22.11.2 and it fixed everything.  I should have known.

Did ssh in and look around.  All seemed well.  Not sure why DNS was so flaky.  But that is for another post.

posts.name: Jarrod Buys
posts.cooked: @bplodiguy How did you go about changing the DNS name to 172.22.11.2?

posts.name: Blaine Pack
posts.cooked: Sorry to be so late replying. Right click on Target.   Choose Properties. Leave the name as Target but change the address to 172.22.11.2 instead of the DNS name.  That fixed it for us.

posts.name: JeffB
posts.cooked: If you do this, make sure you always/only connect via the USB.  Once you do this, you can no longer connect via ethernet.
